xicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play the hypocrite"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dead (especially of an animal)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of نَفَقَ (nafaqa, “to die”)."},"ipa":["/naː.fa.qa/","/naː.fiq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44081","headword_ar":"نَافَقَ","root":"nfq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played the hypocrite"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion: (K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pretended, to the Muslims, that he held the religion of El-Islám, concealing in his heart another religion than El-Islám."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfaqa fulAanFA","text_ar":"نَافَقَ فُلاَنًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted with such a one hypocritically."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dhn","text_ar":"دهن"},{"kind":"text","text":". [But I have not found this elsewhere.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfaqa fiY AlmaHab~api","text_ar":"نَافَقَ فِى المَحَبَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted the hypocrite in respect of love"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har, p. 505.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAna","text_ar":"خَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%82/","headword_ar":"نافقان","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_52","lexicon_en":"Yāqūt al-Ḥamawī, Muʿjam al-Buldān (d. 1229)","lexicon_ar":"معجم البلدان لياقوت الحموي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=147634#695c83","body_html":"نافقان:<br>بالفاء ثم القاف، وآخره نون: من قرى مرو."}]}}